CSS
#13
SELECTOR:
used to find / select elements to set property such as color, height etc.
Selector{ property:value; }  //p{color: blue} 

GROUP OF SELECTORS:
header, footer{
    background-color: yellowgreen;
    border radius: 3px;
}

WAYS TO ADD CSS:
1. INLINE: added directly using style attribute
<p style="color: aqua; background-color: black;"> this line is using inline css styling </p>
2. INTERNAL: css inside 
<head>
    <style>

    </style>
</head>
3. EXTERNAL: CSS kept in a seperate style sheet
create  anew file style.css and add link- 
<head>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>

#PRECEDENCE OR PREFERENCE GIVEN N CASE OF THREE:
 THE LAST LINE EXECUTING 
 TO SPECIFY: ADD  IMPORTANT
 <style>
    body{
        background-color: yellowgreen !important;
    }
</style>


#15
TYPES OF BASIC SELECTORS:
1. CSS ELEMENT SELECTOR:
p{
    color: hotpink;
}

2.ID SELECTOR:
used to select / change only a certain element's id 
its unique, can be accesed as unique id only
<style>
#idSelector{
    background-color: brown;
}
</style>

3.CLASS SELECTOR:
used to select multiple elements properties
it can be accesed by various elements
<style>
     .parabasics{
            background-color: #ee0101;
            color: blueviolet;
            border: 20cm;
        }
</style>

4. GROUPING SELECTORS:

<style>
    footer,span{
            background-color: aqua;
        }
</style>
<body>
    <div>
        <p>PARA 5 /: INSIDE DIV TAG - GROUPing selector 
            Lorem ipsum dolor, sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Dolorem vitae cumque impedit ipsum rerum tempora incidunt beatae, tempore nemo placeat laboriosam delectus eum mollitia alias. Nesciunt iusto quisquam eius dolorem. </p>
    
            <span>SPAN HERE </span>
    <footer> this a footer</footer>
    </div>
</body>

PRECEDENCE/PREFERENCE:
if both id and class taken under saem property then it follows id property

idselector: bg = green ; - class selector: bg = yellow;
=> follows bg = green // ID SELECTOR

COMENTS IN CSS:
/*this is a comment */


#17
FONTS:
<head>
    <style>
        p{
            font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', 'Lucida Sans', Arial, sans-serif;
        }
    </style>
</head>

Font stack:
font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', 'Lucida Sans', Arial, sans-serif;
chooses font based on availabiity (in stack form)

WEB SAFE FONT:
fonts which can be accesed from the web, 
GOOGLE FONTS - can be imported  
Go to google fonts
select a handwritting 
select the type(bold, itlics etc.)
click on plus side of the font text
copy css style sheet link along with accessing link

FONT SIZE:
<style>
    p{
        font size: 10px; // 1/96th of an inch
    }
    </style>

BOLD:
<style>
    p{
        font style: italics;
        font-weight: bold;
    }
</style>


#18
COLORS:
types of color choosing:
1. COLOR BY NAME:
<style>
    #firstpara{
        color: lightcoral;
    }
</style>

2. COLOR BY RGB:
<style>
    #secondpara{
        color: rgb(218, 88, 37);
    }
</style>

3. COLOR BY HEX:
<style>
    #thirdpara{
            color: #50ebeb;
        }
</style>

#19

BORDER:
<style>
/* one line code for border seting */
border: 4px dotted palevioletred;
/* Multiple line code */
border-width: 5px;
border-color: lightsalmon;
border-style: dotted;
/* to curve the borders: border radius */
border-radius: 20px;
</style>

BORDER SIDES:
<style>
border-top: 4px solid lightcoral;
/* border-left, right, bottom:; */
</style>

BORDER RADIUS:
<style>
    border-top - left- radius: 20px;
    /* similarly other radius can also be adjusted */
</style>

BACKGROND POSIION:
<style>
    /* can set a bg img */
     background-image: url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1652641378209-8765ecb1ab5f?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=871&q=80');
     /* to postion the img: */
     background-position: 192px 34px;
     /*postion by pixels or else by the postions: centre, left, right  */
     background-position: center;
     /* can alos postion by x,y */
     background-positon: centre top;
            
</style>

